HEADWORD: Demijohn
<hw>Dem"i*john</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>dame-jeanne</ets>, i.e., Lady Jane, a corruption of Ar.
<ets>damaj⟦amac⟧na</ets>, <ets>damj⟦amac⟧na</ets>, prob. fr.
<ets>Damaghan</ets> a town in the Persian province of Khorassan, once
famous for its glass works.]</ety> <def>A glass vessel or bottle with a
large body and small neck, inclosed in wickerwork.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

